The Architects Registration Council of Nigeria has said that the council registered 694 new architects in three years. A statement on Monday said that the President, ARCON, Oladipupo Ajayi, said this during a valedictory service to mark the end of the three-year tenure of the organisation’s governing council ahead of its inauguration of a new council. The event which held in Abuja was graced by architects and other dignitaries in the financial sector. Ajayi expressed gratitude for the opportunity to lead the council despite the challenges posed by the COVID-19 pandemic. Counting the council’s achievements, he said, “We have seen the register of architects grow, during our leadership, by 694 bringing the number of registered architects to 4926 as at today. “Despite the global pandemic we commenced the renovation of the Lagos office to create a working environment that motivates the members of staff and befits the status of our position as the leader in the built environment. “Only of very recent, we had reclaimed a seemingly lost property and currently in the process of erecting a befitting edifice having successfully had the ground-breaking and foundation laying ceremony on the site carried out personally by the Honourable Minister Federal Ministry of Works, and Housing.” Ajayi disclosed that the council was on the verge of instituting a cooperative society to be anchored by First Bank. Though the council has been disbanded, ARCON stated that the management of would continue to lead the affairs of ARCON until a new council was inaugurated, by the Minister of Works and Housing, Mr Raji Fashola. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com